Uh oh, I somehow failed to give you needed information. Reproducing this problem is rather simple. Create a project, open app/controllers/index.js and just add one line.

{code:java}
function doClick(e) {
    alert($.label.text);
}

//var view = require('Windows.UI.Xaml.Window');
var view = require("Windows.UI.Xaml.Controls.WebView");
$.index.open();
{code}

And build command is:

{code:java}
appc ti build -p windows -T wp-emurator -P MY_PASSWORD -R generated.pfx
{code}

or

{code:java}
appc ti build -p windows -T ws-local -P MY_PASSWORD -R generated.pfx
{code}

I've already provided my environment info above, and I do admit "Windows 10 *61bit*" was weird typo that has been fixed so now you can reproduce this error with serious face ;-)

And one more thing, if you uncomment "Windows.UI.Xaml.Window" line and comment out "Windows.UI.Xaml.Controls.WebView", build ends successfully (only when your build target is wp-emulator or wp-device).
